<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="359" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1950,2012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1950,1976]" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2020" box="[566,686,1950,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviata">
<emphasis box="[566,686,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="359">abbreviata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means abbreviated, referring to the short aedeagal apodeme found in this species.
</paragraph>
